FunctionBlockType.Description: Provides a hysteresis boolean output driven by the difference of two REAL inputs XIN1 and XIN2. If XIN1 exceeds XIN2 by the value specified by input EPS, the output Q is TRUE. The output Q remains TRUE until the input XIN1 is less than the value XIN2, by the value of EPS. FunctionBlockType.Name: INTEGRAL
FunctionBlockType.Description: Integrates the value of input XIN over time. The integration can be reset to a preset value X0 by setting the reset input R1 to true. The CYCLE time defines the time between function block executions. The output XOUT is integrated while the RUN input is true; otherwise the integration value is held. The Q output is true while the integral is not being reset.
